### Task Management API - OAuth Endpoints
### Base URL: http://localhost:8080

### Google OAuth - Redirect to Google
### This will redirect to Google OAuth consent screen
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/auth/oauth/google

###

### Google OAuth Callback - Manual Test
### Note: This is typically called by Google after user consent
### You would get the code and state from the redirect URL
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/auth/oauth/google/callback?code=AUTHORIZATION_CODE_FROM_GOOGLE&state=SECURE_STATE_VALUE

###

### Test OAuth Callback - Missing Parameters
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/auth/oauth/google/callback

###

### Test OAuth Callback - Invalid State
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/auth/oauth/google/callback?code=test_code&state=invalid_state

###

### After OAuth Login - Get Profile
### Use the access token received from OAuth callback
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer ACCESS_TOKEN_FROM_OAUTH_RESPONSE

###

### OAuth User - Get Tasks
### OAuth users can access protected endpoints like regular users
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/tasks
Authorization: Bearer ACCESS_TOKEN_FROM_OAUTH_RESPONSE

###

### OAuth User - Create Task
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/tasks
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer ACCESS_TOKEN_FROM_OAUTH_RESPONSE

{
  "title": "Task created by OAuth user",
  "description": "This task was created by a user who logged in via Google OAuth"
}